abstract: Federal Reserve mistakenly releases staff forecast that shows its own economists are more pessimistic about state of the United States economy than are senior Fed officials who set nation's monetary policy; Fed officials say its inspector general has been asked to investigate leak of confidential report, which was scheduled to remain confidential until 2021.
lead_paragraph: Much of the data, which focused on inflation predictions, initially was released in a form only accessible to users of a particular computer program.

headline.main: Leaked Fed Staff Forecast Reflects Gloomier Expectations for U.S. Economy
